snippet.textDisplay: It's a shame that Shona, Ram and Ruturaj simply used Sambalpuri culture and Odiya Classics for their commercial success. The song 'rangabati' is a tremendous masterpiece, that is visible to all (as even people who don't understand Odiya liked it), but Sona sung so many phrases wrong (mind it phrases, and not just a single word). This simply indicated none of them understood the meaning of the song and thus they ruined the song. The essence, the fun and soul in rangabati was missing. Horrible job! I didn't understand why would one unite a romantic song (rangabati) with a patriotic song (Vande utkala janani- which means worshiping motherland)!!! Who actually was ripped off? Odisha? Sambalpuris? Odiya Culture? Ram Sampath and Sona Mohapatra? Duh!  I hope someday some better person remakes this song paying patronage to culture and respect to the original composition.
